</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2B269EEBDB1448E859DB0616D255FC22" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="1874681CC433A83C051D521FAC40630D" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<taxonomicName id="606AEA100066788B28DCF6A4EFE7A07B" authorityName="group Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa davidi" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidi">Panorpa davidi</taxonomicName>
group Esben-Petersen, 1921: 14; Carpenter, 1938: 268; Cheng, 1957: 5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4E517652A78D7056123DF20EF3CC4467" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" type="emended diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BF1AC3A3C946E13D3EB1B1AE7B575FD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Emended diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="537E08AC1129292CE518EF81DEE6EBA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
The 
<taxonomicName id="9D248F2B4D6B55CB1F29F726CA559287" authorityName="group Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa davidi" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="A900BD786E8AE570E29DC77C4B6FAAF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group can be differentiated from other groups of 
<taxonomicName id="244204CCBBAF839F6319822FB8D9DE69" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B26EC9B5C37EA161CD804AA0CE86A25D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following features: in males, (1) flat notal organ on posterior margin of T3 covering acute postnotal organ on anterior portion of T4; (2) A6 cylindrical, lacking anal horns, mostly projected and setose on dorsal apex; (3) gonostylus with obtuse triangular median tooth and large basal cup on inner margin, (4) elongated dorsal valves of aedeagus with enlarged dorsal processes; and (5) parameres simple, unfurcated, elongated, mostly twisted and crossed mesally; in females, (6) medigynium elongated, broad, with posterior arms distinctly shorter than main plate; and (7) paired lateral basal plates mostly well-developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0B3BFA57C2197A9E6AEAF40832D1D91E" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5954D460C72D3279C852230D69E7E84C" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF41D5BF60FF86FA0A38E9E1DCC2C1BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
Species of the 
<taxonomicName id="D91D92D80606E9AC138CD717A5BCD286" genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="57DE12F7DD43A5616AEEF14DD9AD3C7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group are distributed in the mountainous regions of China, mainly in the Hengduan, Qinling-Bashan, Dalou, Dabie and Taihang mountains (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0C3F7867083F93ECF682696BE6EC0BDC" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Main distribution range of the Panorpa davidi group. A. Hengduan Mountains. B. Qinling-Bashan Mountains. C. Dalou Mountains. D. Dabie Mountains. E. Taihang Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e64325.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/567041" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="BB760763F34E5D46612728763E7589AF" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e64325.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/567041" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="AF7AD6C924C264EC31B1C0AE8B86503F" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis id="01E8CFB59EE7AE4D4CC53666CA0F4089" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Main distribution range of the 
<taxonomicName id="1E24774656D90FD575CA8D719B3EC720" authorityName="group Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa davidi" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="2BA98A91365808F798F53C0A8971ADE3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<emphasis id="23E5B5E608C065E23B8ECA77D693C250" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">A</emphasis>
. Hengduan Mountains. 
<emphasis id="8CFCFCACA51C68356B40F13C959CA0D3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">B</emphasis>
. Qinling-Bashan Mountains. 
<emphasis id="32C27B20A718C6675C3FEC2DFFBA185F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">C</emphasis>
. Dalou Mountains. 
<emphasis id="1161F3D7BA5876E0B5E9E8157A94244E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">D</emphasis>
. Dabie Mountains. 
<emphasis id="3D48A7F99EF9A2DE24FC03B0C80A7490" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">E</emphasis>
. Taihang Mountains.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AE35C3D2AA6F99E4BFD84E36C91746B" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8E2682E898C9AF05EE0AA4889FA6351B" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55083F903A092A833FF5D1E260149A16" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
The 
<taxonomicName id="599C06C1DBCDB1DC60FADCF73FEBEFF2" genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="BB59F3E2A08E8F1E3AA3ACE8E7474D0B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="9A7C8FA2ABCC120EAEDF1305ADCF1378" author="Esben-Petersen, P" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" refId="B11" refString="Esben-Petersen, P, 1921. Mecoptera. Monographic revision: Collections zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps. Catalogue systematique et descriptif 5: 1-172." title="Mecoptera. Monographic revision: Collections zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps. Catalogue systematique et descriptif 5: 1 - 172." year="1921">Esben-Petersen (1921)</bibRefCitation>
to contain 
<taxonomicName id="6BC7A3BD51D3D88C8E4C8CBD868968B9" genus="P." lsidName="P. sibirica" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis id="76BBF027522156656FC62988AEE6F2FC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A1C6C535BEEDBBE6AA1F39B523FB635B" genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="E18E10271D669ACAB511DEE5FECC5A3A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="5E07DBE5198C582CEC37E75E968DFC0C" author="Martynova, OM" journalOrPublisher="Entomologischeskoe Obozreni" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="721 - 747" refId="B30" refString="Martynova, OM, 1957. Skorpionnitzy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR II. Semejstvo Panorpidae. Entomologischeskoe Obozreni 36: 721 - 747" title="Skorpionnitzy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR II. Semejstvo Panorpidae." volume="36" year="1957">Martynova (1957)</bibRefCitation>
later transferred 
<taxonomicName id="8CACFFFC015B6CC1EA853C7A37253F75" genus="P." lsidName="P. sibirica" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis id="AB72FA9F948354C2D619AB6AFFE67A4B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName id="775536192ED4C3081B7100C9E27236DB" genus="Р." lsidName="Р. communis" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="9382D778B9B442218B43968E77083187" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<normalizedToken id="A796855114A1A47C6F6451C4235C179C" originalValue="Р">R</normalizedToken>
. communis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="31E48BBD0883D4F96CD0D1B14FA7212B" author="Carpenter, FM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="267 - 281" refId="B7" refString="Carpenter, FM, 1938. Mecoptera from China, with descriptions of new species. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 40: 267 - 281" title="Mecoptera from China, with descriptions of new species." volume="40" year="1938">Carpenter (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="50D98813551F488C6B10F48771C87443" author="Cheng, FY" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="1 - 117" refId="B9" refString="Cheng, FY, 1957. Revision of the Chinese Mecoptera. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 116: 1 - 117" title="Revision of the Chinese Mecoptera." volume="116" year="1957">Cheng (1957)</bibRefCitation>
, this species group consisted of 19 Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName id="938B6898DAC13D2C04AD15A37AAD55EA" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D812AD61EC059FDAA142424984A4D859" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without anal horn on the posterior margin of T6 in males. Of these, 
<taxonomicName id="07E84AF1138C04FD5A6DCE6E4B648DD0" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa tincta" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tincta">
<emphasis id="CC09E5D2470B1DF1BE21BBD2796A535E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa tincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="A2200B0AFC6F728CACED277CC3170AEE" originalValue="Navás">Navas</normalizedToken>
, 1931 was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="BD87E9C7C51C3101D8AA6A4C65BCC8A4" authorityName="Cai &amp; Hua" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Sinopanorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sinopanorpa" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="485811646C57834B02DCB8149F55407C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Sinopanorpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A82D5000C82B491218BA7EEDC41B04AC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" author="Cai, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="43 - 54" refId="B5" refString="Cai, LJ, Huang, PY, Hua, BZ, 2008. Sinopanorpa, a new genus of Panorpidae (Mecoptera) from the Oriental China with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa 1941: 43 - 54, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" title="Sinopanorpa, a new genus of Panorpidae (Mecoptera) from the Oriental China with descriptions of two new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" volume="1941" year="2008">Cai et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and 12 species that differ remarkably from 
<taxonomicName id="0025F0E43F3D700650A1CEBD32761685" genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="5442621E632E350D2FFC9B449A5AB29D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are herein removed from this group. In this paper, 21 species are recognized in the newly defined 
<taxonomicName id="53CF37A1DCC31E250D956EE3B497B651" genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis id="ACB8C0BBE6A129FF90C6C428C63B9688" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, including 17 known species and four new species.
</paragraph>
